rComments: super smart, great lectures, really nice and encouraged you to discuss work with him and TAs
The course was well organized, The prof encouraged discussion and the material was easy to understand(if you attended class).

Good prof - always encourages discussion (even with some odd questions in this philosophy course). Is very clear what will be on the midterm / final, and it was not a very difficult class because of this. Powerpoints on Blackboard were very useful for getting the most important information. If your in engineering, get this prof for the elective.

I'm pretty sure this was his first time teaching, but he did a good job. His lectures were clear and he is very clear of what will be on his tests. I wasn't a fan of the class just because I don't like philosophy, but he is a good professor.
